Simba the little lion cub lived in the great grasslands of Africa. He loved to play games and gallop around with his group of giggly friends. One day, Simba got separated from his group and he couldn't find his way back. He was getting grumpy and grouchy when he saw a glimmer in the distance. It was the gleaming sun reflecting off a gigantic gem. Simba got curious and began to gallop towards the gem. He soon discovered a group of kindhearted giraffes who welcomed him with great generosity. Simba felt grateful and gleeful to have made new friends in the great grasslands of Africa.
